Let `v` and `v'` be sections of the tangent bundle of manifolds `M` and `M'`, respectively, and let  `f : M â†’ M'` be a differentiable map. Then `f` maps integral curves of `v` to integral curves of `v'` if and only if `v` and `v'` are `f`-related.
